  "steps": [
    {
      "order": 1,
      "instruction": "Cut pork into thin slices. If using pork shoulder, as I did, halve it lengthwise to form two long pieces, then slice the pieces. See photo below."
    },
    {
      "order": 2,
      "instruction": "Combine Marinade ingredients in a bowl. Add pork. Marinate for 30 minutes, or overnight."
    },
    {
      "order": 3,
      "instruction": "To cook, heat oil in a large non stick skillet (Note 4) over high heat. Add garlic and onion, cook for 2 minutes until translucent. Add pork and cook for 5 minutes or until dark golden and caramelised, and just cooked through."
    },
    {
      "order": 4,
      "instruction": "Serve immediately with rice - or for a low carb, low cal option, try Cauliflower Rice! Garnish with sliced shallots and sesame seeds."
    }
  ]
